INSERT INTO `sub_headings` (`id`, `article_id`, `heading_id`, `name`, `content`, `author`, `reading_time`, `date`) VALUES
('1dd59d7c-78d2-4c22-9b74-e4634f7d83e2', 'Goods And Services Tax', 'Introduction to GST', 'Taxable Person under GST', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">In the context of GST, a ‘taxable person’ encompasses a diverse range of entities engaged in business activities within India. This definition includes individuals, companies, firms, trusts, government bodies, and more involved in economic activities like trade and commerce. Whether you are registered or required to register under the GST Act, you are considered a taxable person if you partake in such activities. This category extends to entities such as HUF, LLP, AOP/BOI, foreign corporations, cooperative societies, local authorities, trusts, and artificial juridical persons. Understanding your role as a taxable person is vital for seamless GST compliance and navigating the regulatory landscape effectively.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Who needs to Register for GST in India?</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Discover whether you need to register for GST in India. It is mandatory for the following categories:</span></strong></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Businesses selling goods with an annual turnover exceeding ₹40 lakhs (₹20 lakhs for specific states)*</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Businesses providing services with an annual turnover exceeding ₹20 lakhs (₹10 lakhs for certain states)</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Individuals previously registered under older tax laws (Excise, VAT, Service Tax, etc.)</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">New owners of a registered business in case of transfer or demerger</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Suppliers conducting inter-state transactions</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Casual taxable persons</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Non-resident taxable persons</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Agents acting on behalf of a supplier</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Taxpayers paying tax under the reverse charge mechanism</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Input service distributors</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">E-Commerce operators/aggregators**</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Persons supplying through e-commerce aggregators</span></strong></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 18px;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Providers of online information and database access or retrieval (OIDAR) services from outside India to someone in India, except registered taxable persons</span><br><br></strong><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\"><strong style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Note:</strong></span></span><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"> Registration is not mandatory if your business exclusively deals with exempted goods/services under GST. </span><br><br></strong><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\"><strong style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Important update:</strong></span></span><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"> In Budget 2023, section 23 of the CGST Act was amended retrospectively from 1st July 2017. This clarification states that individuals mentioned in section 23 are not required to register even if they meet conditions mentioned in sections 22(1) and 24 of the CGST Act.</span><br></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><br>*Some Normal Category states maintain the existing limit of ₹20 lakhs, while some Special Category states have opted for an increased limit of ₹40 lakhs. <br><br>**Attention e-commerce sellers/aggregators: You do not need to register if your total sales are less than ₹20 lakhs. (Notification No. 65/2017 – Central Tax dated 15th November 2017)</span></strong></p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">GST Registration</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Understanding the GST registration process for various taxable persons is crucial for a tax professional. According to GST regulations, every individual or business must apply for registration in each State where they are liable within thirty days of becoming eligible.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Special consideration is required for casual or non-resident taxable persons; they should apply at least five days before commencing their business activities.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">It is important to note that the GST registration number is PAN-based, making having a PAN a prerequisite for obtaining registration.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">To ensure efficient compliance, each taxable person should obtain separate registration for each State, as GST registration is state-wise.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Moreover, taxpayers can obtain separate registrations for each business vertical within the same State, providing flexibility and clarity in compliance, especially for businesses operating in multiple sectors.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ecfaca63-7fff-0df9-06af-7009cb2e1c57\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Trust Calcya as your partner in achieving GST registration success. Subscribe now for the latest updates and expert advice on GST and taxation.</span></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br class=\"Apple-interchange-newline\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></p>', 'Admin', '9', '2024-05-07'),
('2902116a-3a0f-4440-98c5-cafbe4c896e1', 'Alternative Dispute Resolution', 'What is Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR)?', 'What is Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR)?', '<p style=\"line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR) is an innovative approach strategically designed to furnish an alternative channel for dispute resolution, distinct from conventional court-based proceedings. The term “alternative” underscores the critical element of choice individuals possess when opting for different dispute resolution methodologies, effectively diverging from the traditional courtroom procedures while concurrently establishing a court-adjunct process.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Why is ADR Necessary?</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">ADR serves as a vital lifeline for parties entangled in disputes, offering a facilitative platform for issue resolution supported by an impartial third party. It emerges as a swifter and cost-effective alternative to conventional litigation, extending the scope for adaptable and innovative solutions tailored to individual needs and objectives.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Harmonious Resolutions: The Impact of Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR)</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">In nations such as India, individuals on the fringes of society often grapple with access to justice due to financial constraints and a lack of familiarity with legal proceedings. In this context, Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR) emerges as a beacon of hope, alleviating the strain on overburdened courts and delivering efficient, accessible, and timely resolutions that transcend demographic boundaries.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">The Quest for Alternative Dispute Resolution</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Inevitably, the fabric of human interactions is woven with the threads of conflicts and disputes. Disputes are, consequently, an inescapable facet of societal existence. The inexorable necessity becomes apparent – these disputes must be resolved with minimal expenditure regarding financial resources and time allocation. The overarching goal is to reserve an ample share of time and resources for constructive and productive pursuits.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">The Emergence of ADR</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Addressing these concerns, legal systems worldwide have been established wherein individuals seeking redressal for grievances are encouraged to seek recourse through the courts. This framework is built on the bedrock principle that a remedy should be readily available wherever a wrong is committed, thereby mitigating the impulse for individuals to resort to self-help measures. Regrettably, the overwhelming caseload in the judicial system has rendered it congested and prone to inefficiencies, prompting the quest for alternative pathways.</span></strong></p><p style=\"line-height: 2;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 18px;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><br></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">ADR: A Swift and Effective Solution</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 18px;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">The quest for alternatives to the traditional courtroom setting ushered in a plethora of quasi-judicial and administrative tribunals, furnishing expedited mechanisms for relief. These tribunals represent alternatives within the realm of dispute resolution, although they, too, grapple with congestion and the consequent delays in dispensing remedies. For instance, in employment matters, relief often materialises post-retirement, rendering the compensation insufficient to compensate for the period of service lost. Another avenue, the consumer forum, emerged to provide swift and cost-effective remedies to consumers aggrieved by the quality of goods and services. Alas, the sheer volume of complaints inundated these forums, resulting in substantial delays in addressing consumer concerns.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 18px;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">The Role of Calcya in ADR</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 2; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-c651407d-7fff-c4ed-e10e-77ada9e66bb7\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Embrace the realm of ADR and make it an exciting and manageable journey for all stakeholders involved. Place your trust in Calcya’s expertise in Alternative Dispute Resolution to navigate the path towards harmonious conflict resolution, where every facet of the discussion is considered, ensuring that no element is left unaddressed.</span></strong></p>', 'Admin', '6', '2024-05-01'),
('463456ef-6ab8-4663-8ebe-ecde0234c8f2', 'Goods And Services Tax', 'Introduction to GST', 'GST Simplified: Making Taxes Easy for Everyone', '<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-eb144d0b-7fff-b36e-4965-e45ac1567d22\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Taxes can be a bit confusing, but do not worry! Let us explore Goods and Services Tax (GST) together. GST is a vital tax system in India that aims to make taxes simpler and fairer for everyone.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Introducing Goods and Services Tax</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">GST is a fantastic tax system that simplifies how we pay taxes. It combines many different taxes, making it easier for businesses and individuals to understand and follow. It replaces taxes like excise duty, VAT, and service tax.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Why is it Called Goods and Services Tax?</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">GST covers goods (things we buy) and services (people do for us). Having one tax for both ensures fairness and uniformity. This helps businesses and individuals know what to expect regarding taxes.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Simplifying Taxes for a Brighter Future</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">GST is like a superhero that fights against complicated taxes. It helps businesses grow, and people understand taxes easily. When things are more straightforward, we can focus on more important things, like learning, playing, and building a better country.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">GST is a unique tax system that simplifies taxes for everyone. It makes paying taxes easier to understand and ensures fairness. By embracing GST, we can all contribute to a better future. So let us navigate the world of GST together and make taxes a little less confusing and much more manageable!</span></p></strong><br></p>', 'Admin', '1', '2024-05-01'),
('51ab1008-13ab-446b-a3af-619512fb1677', 'Alternative Dispute Resolution', 'What is Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR)?', 'Scope of ADR', '<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 24px;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-e84bd39a-7fff-f277-11ca-eec0de8fb82b\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Introduction</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR) occupies a pivotal space within the spectrum of legal alternatives. It serves as a crucial bridge, providing an escape from traditional litigation and enriching the arbitration landscape. This exploration delves into the dynamic realm of ADR, where it transcends traditional boundaries, influences other dispute-resolution mechanisms, and champions a more flexible and efficient approach to resolving conflicts.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">ADR’s Origins and Evolution</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">At its inception, arbitration emerged as a pragmatic refuge from the complexities of litigation. However, its evolution has led to a process closely resembling court proceedings, laden with statutory demands. To truly understand ADR, we must recognise its role in transcending the adjudicatory process, even when not entirely consensual. ADR calls for the intervention of an impartial third party skilled in conciliation, mediation, or negotiation, adept at orchestrating reconciliation and crafting resolutions that reflect the parties’ collaboration.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">The Foundational Role of Arbitration</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Arbitration remains a vital alternative to litigation. It serves as a cornerstone in the study of alternative dispute resolution. Beyond providing substantive resolutions, it profoundly influences the procedural contours of other alternative methods. Arbitration’s principles and practices have significantly informed the development of ancillary and hybrid processes within the dispute resolution landscape.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Defying Categorisation</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">ADR defies easy categorisation—it represents a dispute resolution technique where a third party’s decision lacks legally binding force on the disputants. While mediation is a notable facet, ADR encompasses diverse approaches. ADR neither mimics the formalism of litigation nor replicates arbitration’s structured procedures. Its allure lies in its flexibility and agility, a stark departure from the entrenched norms of litigation.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">The ADR Advantage</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">In the face of exorbitant legal fees, interminable court processes, and the inherent inflexibility of litigation, ADR emerges as a beacon of hope. It strives to provide parties with a cost-effective, expeditious, and less bureaucratic avenue for redress. ADR’s fundamental purpose is to tailor remedies to the unique contours of each case, making it a compelling alternative to arbitration and litigation.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">The scope of ADR extends far beyond conventional legal boundaries, championing principles of fairness, equity, and efficiency at the heart of dispute resolution. As a dynamic instrument of justice, ADR’s influence continues to expand, redefining how we navigate conflicts and reaffirming its central role in the legal landscape.</span></p></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><br></span></p>', 'Admin', '2', '2024-05-01');
INSERT INTO `sub_headings` (`id`, `article_id`, `heading_id`, `name`, `content`, `author`, `reading_time`, `date`) VALUES
('7d750681-8f72-404b-93c4-44b571c4d598', 'Goods And Services Tax', 'Introduction to GST', 'Non-resident Taxable Person under GST', '<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-146959af-7fff-dc00-c37e-579ce9914bc4\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Are you a business importing goods or services from outside India or managing a business on behalf of a resident outside India? If so, this article is relevant to you. At Calcya, we understand the complexities of GST compliance for non-resident taxable persons and are here to help.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Who is a ‘Non-Resident Taxable Person’?</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Under GST, a ‘non-resident taxable person’ refers to any individual or business that occasionally undertakes transactions involving the supply of goods or services, or both, whether as a principal, agent, or in any other capacity, but who has no fixed place of business or residence in India.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">In simpler words, this includes all businesses supplying goods, services, or data retrieval services from outside India, making them fall under the purview of the Goods and Services Tax law.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">According to Section 24 of the CGST Act, certain businesses and entities are required to register under GST. They are not governed by the minimum threshold limit of ₹20 lakhs/10 lakhs. Thus, irrespective of whether the business is involved in a one-time transaction or frequent taxable transactions, every non-resident individual or company must obtain a registration under the Goods and Services Tax.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Registration Process for a Non-Resident Taxable Person</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Every person or business that falls under the definition covered above needs to apply for registration at least five days prior to the commencement of business. Further clarification has been provided in case of a high-sea sale; the law says that every person who makes a supply from the territorial waters of India shall obtain registration in the coastal state or Union territory where the nearest point of the appropriate baseline is located. High Sea Sale (HSS) is a sale carried out by the carrier document consignee to another buyer. At the same time, the goods are still being transported or after their dispatch from the port/airport of origin and before they arrive at the port/airport of destination.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">A non-resident taxable person needs to electronically submit a duly signed application, along with a self-attested copy of his valid passport, for registration using the form GST REG-09 at least five days before the commencement of business on the Common Portal. The application must be duly signed or verified through EVC, a new mode of electronic verification based on Aadhar. The non-resident (if it is a company) must submit the tax identification number of its original country (whatever is the equivalent of our PAN in that country).</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">A person applying for registration as a non-resident taxable person will be given a temporary reference number electronically by the Common Portal for making an advance tax deposit in his electronic cash ledger. An acknowledgement will be issued after that.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Advance Payment of Tax by Non-Resident Taxable Person</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">A non-resident taxable person must make an advance deposit of tax in an amount equivalent to the estimated tax liability of such a person for the period for which registration is sought.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">In other words, registration rules circulated by the GST council have specified that every person registered as a non-resident taxable person is required to deposit tax in advance on a presumption basis. This advance tax will get credited into the Electronic Cash Ledger. It will eventually be adjusted against the actual tax liability when return filing.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">These rules further specify that in case a non-resident taxable person intends to extend the period of registration indicated in their application for registration, an application using the form GST REG-11 should be furnished electronically through the Common Portal before the end of the validity of registration granted to him.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">By understanding the requirements and procedures related to ‘Non-Resident Taxable Person,’ businesses can ensure seamless compliance with the GST law.&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">At Calcya, we strive to simplify GST compliance for non-resident taxable persons. Trust our expertise to guide you through the registration and compliance process, ensuring a seamless experience conducting business in India. Stay informed, stay compliant – join our community and let us be your trusted tax partner!</span></p></strong', 'Admin', '3', '2024-05-02'),
('ab484e92-2d76-4965-b562-36c625d1414e', 'Goods And Services Tax', 'Introduction to GST', 'Casual Taxable Person (CTP) under GST', '<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6a882edf-7fff-92de-4225-3028cae25ce3\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">In the context of GST, a ‘taxable person’ encompasses a diverse range of entities engaged in business activities within India. This definition includes individuals, companies, firms, trusts, government bodies, and more involved in economic activities like trade and commerce. Whether you are registered or required to register under the GST Act, you are considered a taxable person if you partake in such activities. This category extends to entities such as HUF, LLP, AOP/BOI, foreign corporations, cooperative societies, local authorities, trusts, and artificial juridical persons. Understanding your role as a taxable person is vital for seamless GST compliance and navigating the regulatory landscape effectively.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Who needs to Register for GST in India?</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Discover whether you need to register for GST in India. It is mandatory for the following categories:</span></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Businesses selling goods with an annual turnover exceeding ₹40 lakhs (₹20 lakhs for specific states)*</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Businesses providing services with an annual turnover exceeding ₹20 lakhs (₹10 lakhs for certain states)</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Individuals previously registered under older tax laws (Excise, VAT, Service Tax, etc.)</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">New owners of a registered business in case of transfer or demerger</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Suppliers conducting inter-state transactions</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Casual taxable persons</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Non-resident taxable persons</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Agents acting on behalf of a supplier</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Taxpayers paying tax under the reverse charge mechanism</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; font-size: 12pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Input service distributors</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); ', 'Admin', '3', '2024-05-11'),
('f1e473ec-0ec7-4b6d-a56b-ed3c9e310351', 'Goods And Services Tax', 'Introduction to GST', 'Input Service Distributor (ISD) under GST', '<p><br></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">As a tax professional, comprehending the vital role of an Input Service Distributor (ISD) within the GST framework becomes imperative for effective credit allocation and adherence to compliance. The ISD assumes a significant responsibility in distributing Input Tax Credit (ITC) to its branches, each holding distinct GSTINs but operating under the same PAN. This strategic practice empowers businesses with shared expenses and centralised billing to streamline credit acquisition and ensure a seamless flow of credit under the GST regime.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Who qualifies as an Input Service Distributor (ISD) under GST?</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Understanding the criteria for an ISD becomes paramount for businesses aiming to maximise their credit distribution efficiency. An ISD denotes a taxpayer receiving invoices for services utilised by its branches. Subsequently, it allocates the applicable tax paid as ITC to these branches via ISD invoices. The branches must share the same PAN as the ISD while having different GSTINs. This streamlined process eases credit retrieval for entities and strengthens the seamless flow of credit within the GST framework.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Situations where ISD is not applicable</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Though the ISD facilitates credit distribution, specific scenarios restrict its applicability. It is important to note that the ISD cannot distribute ITC concerning inputs and capital goods, including raw materials and machinery. Furthermore, ITC distribution to outsourced manufacturers or service providers is not permissible.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Benefits of Registering as ISD</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">ISD registration offers many benefits for businesses seeking simplified credit distribution and centralised billing. Embracing this facility streamlines credit acquisition and bolsters the smooth flow of credit within the GST system. By opting for ISD registration, businesses can optimise credit allocation and navigate the complexities of credit distribution.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Conditions for ISD Registration</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Achieving seamless credit allocation requires adhering to specific conditions for ISD registration. Apart from regular GST registration, entities must mandatorily register separately as an “ISD” and declare this status in the REG-01 form under serial number 14. This transparent approach ensures compliance with GST norms and seamless credit allocation.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Process of Credit Distribution by ISD</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">ISDs distribute tax credits to recipients through the issuance of ISD invoices. Crucially, the amount of tax credit distributed must not exceed the credit available with the ISD by the end of a relevant month. To ensure accuracy and efficiency, this information is accessible from the GSTR-2B return.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Restrictions on Credit Distribution</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Despite facilitating credit allocation, certain limitations apply to the ISD process. Notably, credit of tax paid under the reverse charge mechanism cannot be distributed to recipients. Instead, ISDs must utilise such credit as regular taxpayers.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 24px;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 14pt;\">Allocation of CGST, IGST, and SGST Credit</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">To ensure equitable credit distribution, specific input services exclusively utilised by one recipient can only be allocated to that particular entity. For input services commonly utilised by multiple recipients, allocation occurs proportionately based on their operational turnover during the year. This equitable practice ensures the fair distribution of tax credits.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Recovery Procedure for Wrongful Distribution of Credit</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">In situations involving inappropriate credit distribution by an ISD, such as surpassing available credit or improper allocation, the excess credit must be recovered from recipients alongside interest. Strict adherence to the ‘Demand and Recovery’ provisions facilitates efficient credit management.</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">A thorough understanding of ISD intricacies is pivotal for impeccable tax compliance. As a tax professional, ensure your clients adeptly navigate ISD regulations and optimise tax credit allocation for seamless business operations.&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-f86fd4a0-7fff-d92b-cfce-aea47bb59ab8\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Subscribe now for expert guidance, ensuring compliance with GST norms while maximising tax efficiency.</span></strong></p><p><br></p><br class=\"Apple-interchange-newline\">', 'Admin', '6', '2024-05-02'),
('ff360be3-2ea1-4e9b-9b1f-ccfded0b84e4', 'Alternative Dispute Resolution', 'What is Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR)?', 'Popularity of ADR', '<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 18px;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-030d184b-7fff-1613-e3bf-925365677b52\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">In the contemporary legal and business environment, the surge in Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR) represents a transformative response to the challenges of our time. This dynamic shift is driven by the growing realisation that traditional litigation processes often prove slow, costly, and ill-suited to address the complexities of the modern world.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">The origins of modern-day ADR can be traced back to the late 20th century, a period marked by rapid advancements in science and technology. This era of innovation not only revolutionised industries but also intensified global competition and raised concerns about consumer rights. In the face of such rapid change, the traditional legal system, steeped in centuries-old traditions, struggled to keep pace with the evolving landscape.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">As a strategic answer to these challenges, ADR emerges as a game-changer. At its core, ADR excels in delivering cost-effective and expeditious solutions, unburdened by the constraints of traditional legal procedures.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">At the heart of ADR lies a collaborative approach. It encourages parties to open dialogue, seeking mutually acceptable resolutions rather than protracted courtroom battles. This collaborative spirit extends to the involvement of impartial third parties, such as mediators or arbitrators, who expertly guide constructive conversations toward resolution.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">The versatility of ADR further underscores its relevance. It can be applied to various disputes, from commercial and contractual matters to intricate family conflicts and multifaceted international disputes. In cases where traditional litigation falls short, such as disputes involving shared interests or spanning multiple jurisdictions, ADR emerges as a flexible and effective alternative.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">Moreover, ADR’s non-binding nature empowers disputing parties with a degree of control over their outcomes. It encourages the exploration of creative solutions and often preserves relationships that adversarial litigation may irreparably damage.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.7999999999999998;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\">The surge in ADR reflects a seismic shift toward a more adaptable and client-focused approach to dispute resolution. It stands as a testament to the legal profession’s capacity to evolve with the times and deliver justice that is accessible and efficient. As the legal landscape continues to evolve, ADR remains at the forefront, offering a dynamic path to resolution as diverse as the challenges it confronts.</span></p></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></p>', 'Admin', '3', '2024-05-26');

